<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="569" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Discussion.</emphasis>
A single male (
<figureCitation box="[540,642,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[150,1435,988,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,988,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Lectotypes of three of Thunberg’s species and selected relevant labels. 1 – 3, Lygaeus ater Thunberg, 1822; 4 – 5, Lygaeus biguttatus Thunberg, 1822; 6 – 7, Cimex caffer Thunberg, 1784. Scales in mm; labels not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231514/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
Fig. 
<number box="[600,642,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
) is present in Thunberg’s collection in 
<collectionCode box="[1134,1206,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">UPSZ</collectionCode>
. The brief original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[313,458,297,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lygaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[313,458,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lygaeus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits well with this specimen, except the fore wings which are not completely devoid of spots (“immaculatus hemelytris opacis”). Based on the ancient handwritten label pinned next to the specimen (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[150,1435,988,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,988,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Lectotypes of three of Thunberg’s species and selected relevant labels. 1 – 3, Lygaeus ater Thunberg, 1822; 4 – 5, Lygaeus biguttatus Thunberg, 1822; 6 – 7, Cimex caffer Thunberg, 1784. Scales in mm; labels not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231514/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) it is considered as part of the original 
<typeStatus box="[604,652,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">type</typeStatus>
series and it is hereby designated as a 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1193,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
