<bibRefCitation author="Slater" box="[1012,1170,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" refString="Slater, J. A. (1964) A catalogue of the Lygaeidae of the world. Vols. I. - II. University of Connecticut, Storrs, xviii + 1668 pp. [I: i - xviii, 1 - 778, II: 779 - 1668]" type="book chapter" year="1964">
Slater (
<number box="[1104,1162,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pericart" box="[1248,1432,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" refString="Pericart, J. (2001) Family Lygaeidae Schilling, 1829 - Seed-bugs. In: Aukema, B. &amp; Rieger, Chr. (Eds.), Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 4. Pentatomomorpha I. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, pp. 35 - 220." type="book" year="2001">
Péricart (
<number box="[1363,1424,440,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Reexamination of the 
<typeStatus box="[417,465,477,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">type</typeStatus>
material revealed that the act of 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal" box="[875,1005,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" refString="Stal, C. (1855) Om Thunbergska Hemipterarter. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 12 (7), 345 - 347." type="journal article" year="1855">
Stål (
<number box="[939,997,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1855.0">1855</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was erroneous, 
<taxonomicName box="[1205,1355,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lygaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[1205,1355,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lygaeus ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName box="[353,469,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Aellopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis box="[353,469,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">A. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The spiracles and trichobothria undoubtedly indicate that it belongs to the tribe Lethaeini.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
Since all members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dallas, 1852" authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1852" box="[452,705,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lethaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[452,553,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lethaeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dallas" box="[562,705,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" refString="Dallas, W. S. (1852) List of the specimens of hemipterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part II. Trustees of the British Museum, London, pp. 369 - 592, plates xii - xv." type="book chapter" year="1852">
Dallas, 
<number box="[649,705,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1852.0">1852</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and related genera are known from macropterous morphs only, brachyptery is an unusual character of this species. Several characters, particularly the shape of the head, the absence of a pronotal collar, the absence of anterolateral setae of the pronotum, as well as the hemelytral colour, and the armature of the fore femora, still suggest that in spite of the reduced wings it belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1367,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lethaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1266,1367,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lethaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a consequence, the new combination 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunberg, 1822" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1822" box="[547,904,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lethaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[547,699,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lethaeus ater</emphasis>
(Thunberg, 
<number box="[837,897,728,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1822.0">1822</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[916,1043,727,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,1043,727,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is hereby proposed. The species is apparently not conspecific with any other described species of 
<taxonomicName box="[854,955,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lethaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,955,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lethaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="569" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">
<taxonomicName authority="Slater, 1964" authorityName="Slater" authorityYear="1964" box="[199,543,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Lethaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barberi">
<emphasis box="[199,394,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">Lethaeus barberi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Slater" box="[404,543,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" refString="Slater, J. A. (1964) A catalogue of the Lygaeidae of the world. Vols. I. - II. University of Connecticut, Storrs, xviii + 1668 pp. [I: i - xviii, 1 - 778, II: 779 - 1668]" type="book chapter" year="1964">
Slater, 
<number box="[485,543,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, another brachypterous species of Lethaeini from 
<collectingCountry box="[1126,1275,799,824]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, based on the reexamination of its 
<typeStatus box="[397,495,836,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34994" box="[659,738,837,860]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34994" name="Lund University" pageId="2" pageNumber="569">MZLU</collectionCode>
certainly does not belong to this genus as its pronotum is provided with a rather narrow collar and anterolateral setae. Currently it is not possible to place this species with confidence in any existing genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
